Sentencas: Anode support is prepared using phase inversion method and directly used for anode supported solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: High Current Density of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Anode Support via Phase Inversion Method

Sentencas: The anode substrate is about 560 mu m in thickness and has a porosity of 60.0%.
Titulo: High Current Density of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Anode Support via Phase Inversion Method

Sentencas: The finger-like pore layer is 522 mu m in thickness, in which the finger-like pore diameter is about 30 mu m.
Titulo: High Current Density of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Anode Support via Phase Inversion Method

Sentencas: The sponge layer is 28 mu m in thickness and has a porosity of 46.1%.
Titulo: High Current Density of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Anode Support via Phase Inversion Method

Sentencas: The single cell with Ni-YSZ/YSZ/GDC/BaCo0.4Fe0.4Zr0.1Y0.1O3-delta configuration is fabricated with YSZ electrolyte on the skin layer.
Titulo: High Current Density of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Anode Support via Phase Inversion Method

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C and under an output voltage of 0.64 V, the single cell attains a power density of 3.33 W cm(-2).
Titulo: High Current Density of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Anode Support via Phase Inversion Method

Sentencas: At 700 degrees C, 750 degrees C and 800 degrees C, the single cell outputs a current density over 5.2 A cm(-2) without the appearance of limited current density from gas transport.
Titulo: High Current Density of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Anode Support via Phase Inversion Method

Sentencas: The results depict gas transport in the anode substrate with the sponge layer and the skin layer is highly efficient.
Titulo: High Current Density of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Anode Support via Phase Inversion Method
